From: ElegooSlicer Builder <builder@elegoo.com>
Date: Wed, 2 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] elegoolink: add missing #include <algorithm>

GCC 16 no longer implicitly includes <algorithm> through other headers.
The elegoolink event_system.h uses std::find_if without including <algorithm>,
causing compilation failure with:

  error: 'find_if' is not a member of 'std'

---
 include/events/event_system.h | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/include/events/event_system.h
+++ b/include/events/event_system.h
@@ -1,5 +1,6 @@
 #pragma once
+#include <algorithm>
 
 #include <functional>
 #include <unordered_map>
